      <TEXTAREA NAME="body" ROWS="15"
        COLS="50" WRAP="virtual">>There are three distinct guard camps in 
>EK: 
>1) Human camp near the gorge leading 
>to Beholder. This is a village 
>of sorts, a cluster of houses 
>around which 2 or 3 guards 
>are posted at separate spots. Each 
>can be pulled alone without interference 
>from the others. 
>2) Human camp, up the road from 
>the bridge and a little to 
>the North. This camp is another 
>human house cluster, again with 2 
>or 3 guards that can be 
>pulled by themselves. 
>3) Barbarian fishing village, at the end 
>of the coastline. You can reach 
>this spot by turning right while 
>on the bridge and facing into 
>the zone. Run all the way 
>down the beach until you encounter 
>this series of barbarian huts. There 
>are 3 guards here which can 
>be pulled alone, but doing so 
>requires a bit of careful timing 
>(one of them roams the perimeter 
>and must be cleared first). 
>Each of the guard spots is about 
>as good for exp as the 
>next, and the guards in each 
>spot are the same in terms 
>of loot and experience. They are 
>level 35 or thereabouts, and they 
>usually drop up to 4 platinum, 
>with the occasional research word or 
>piece of bronze armor/weaponry. 
>Hope this helps. :) 
>~Kefka Zinn Necromonitor Staff 
</TEXTAREA>
     
   </TD></TR>
